$ MS Access Option: ANSI-92 compatibility

The SQL compatibility mode (which by default is → misc/ISO/9075#sql-89[SQL 89, level 1] can be upgraded to SQL-92 under File -> Options -> Object Designers -> SQL Server Compatible Syntax (ANSI 92):
gh|about-Access|/options/ANSI-92-compatibility.png||

{ Chaning the option with Visual Basic for Application

  IN VBA, it is possible to set this options like so:
code {
setOption "ANSI Query Mode", 1
code }

 `setOption` is defined in the → Microsoft/Office/Access/Object-Model/Application[`Application`] object. Because this object is the default object, it does not need to be specified.

}
